Let's wait and see where she takes us next, knowing Taylor, it will be AMAZING. •REPUTATION Tour dates: 5/8/18 •1989 World Tour dates: Santa Clara 8/15/15 and Glendale 8/17/15 •RED Tour dates: Glendale 5/29/13. ✨STAY POSITIVE✨

body:
✨Excited AF for TS7💛💗✨

Not only just to get more music from Taylor, and along with it some insight to her life, but because we have NEVER had music from Taylor during a long term relationship before and I’m positive she will share!! (Some anyways)

We’ve had plenty of music from her AFTER relationship, during the beginning of them, and a sneak peak of her finding true love in the last album, but NEVER have we been blessed with music from her about the complexity of relationships that last and take work.

I’m so so so intrigued by the thought that we will get music from Taylor about a relationship that has lasted for over 2-3 years. Her first true long term love with a man who she wants to be his end game.. this is completely uncharted territory for her. And us.

We’ve never had music from Taylor about the trials and tribulations of a LASTING love…

One where you have a fairytale love and things are amazing because you’re with the right person, but also where you’ve been together long enough to have had real struggles and have to come to terms that your significant other isn’t actually PERFECT and vice versa .. One where you see their flaws for what they are, and you accept and maybe even love those too in time. One where you weren’t sure if all the crap you’ve put each other through would be worth it to them to stay because you’re out of the “honeymoon phase.” One where you’ve had to work together and fight for the relationship to function now, where things aren’t as easy as they were in the beginning. Things are so real now and real love takes work. One where you’ve put everything you had into it and so did the other person and you look at each other knowing that THATS your person… you know that together you are stronger. You’re better with them. One where it didnt happen by accident, it took effort everyday to make it to where you are now. One where you built that relationship brick by brick, each brick being a unique challenge you two overcame and then sculpted with your love and teamwork to fit your relationship’s architectural need, you build upwards by hand, each brick built by your love, until it turned into a fortress for the two of you to rule your empire behind. One where you two were faced with problems that only you two could solve together and each problem faced and conquered brought you closer and more together than ever before. Each time you grow together. One where you can only achieve complete and true comfort because you two have gone through it all, seen the best and the worst of each other and still made it out together and happy and strong.

That’s what Taylor is experiencing and I cannot wait for her to get real with her love and share these kind of stories

summary: just wondering, how did you get into taylor swift?
question: just wondering, how did you get into taylor swift?
answer:
ooh good question. i heard about her the first time back in 2012 i think? i was in algebra with @southerndreamsofstarlight and she mentioned her and that was the first time i’d actually heard about her,,,, i guess i was a really sheltered homeschooler back them lmaoo. i didn’t listen to her music until around 2014 because i was mostly a theatre kid yeet. but i mostly listened to just her hit songs.

i only really got into her music last year when she released reputation and i really liked it, and i went back and listened to her older stuff. then in late october i had some prize money i won from a speech & drama competition and i made a really on the whim decision to go to the rep tour on 9 november, so i basically got tickets literally less than 2 weeks before the show. probably the most spontaneous thing i’ve ever done. and the best thing, too. because that was the coolest show i’ve ever been too. i’m still shook that i saw @taylorswift with my own two eyes.

and after that i was just. sold. fell head over heels with her and that’s pretty why my blog now straddles this weird middle ground of taylor swift and musical theatre. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯

i’m still a very new swiftie tho, so if you ever wanna hmu and talk about taylor, please feel free to do so. hoho.
